Global Reusable Straws Market Insights
Reusable Straws Market Market size was valued at USD 2.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 4.0 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 6.4% from 2024 to 2030.

Reusable Straws Market Overview
The reusable straws market has been expanding steadily, valued at USD 3.16 billion in 2023, and is projected to reach USD 9.98 billion by 2030, with a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 17.8% during the forecast period. The rising demand for sustainable alternatives to single-use plastic products is one of the key factors driving this growth. Increased awareness about environmental issues, coupled with government regulations restricting the use of plastic, has made reusable straws a popular choice across industries like hospitality, foodservice, and retail. Market players are innovating with various materials, such as stainless steel, bamboo, and silicone, to meet consumer preferences for eco-friendly products.

